Initial Commit

Far from complete. Just committing to track changes.

releases.body:
Minor fixes.

* Fixed some title cross-pollination problems when quick switching between items.
* Changed "opening" to "closing" in a save confirm popup.

Save changes. Some other changes. Lots of fixes. Live the dream.

CHANGELOG:

* Changed to manual saving
* Added 5-min autosave
* Added need-save indicated (*) after filename.
* Asks to save before opening new files, etc.
* Collapsed nests save their state now.
* Fixed title update for file loading (I think)
* Fixed save-on-close nuking the file.
* Fixed removing nested items.
* Fixed display of orphaned items (ORPHANS SAVED!)
* Probably some other stuff.
* Minor fixes (MYSTERY FLAVOR!)

Icon doesn't seem to want to work on Linux? Not sure why.

EDIT: Release contains save fix commit.

Alright. A Proper v0.7.3
- Made item loading generic, saved about 200 lines of redundant code. Add/Remove still type specific at the moment.
- Added a manual focusout trigger when user mouses over the item list since loading an item wasn't always triggering focusout. It's fine. It works. Whatever.

That's it.

22 Jan 2017
UPDATED LINUX BUILDS.

Simple thing
- Autocomplete now ignores diacritic marks.
- Filtering lists now ignores diacritic marks.
- It's going to snow tomorrow and they don't plow the roads around here

Alright. Back to work on the book.

Right, let's a-go:
- Spellchecking
- With add-to-dictionary stuff
- Default file name for new files.
- Shut up.
- New context menu handler.
- Fixed hitting return in non-big edit blocks

That's it.
Just fixed a new file issue on Linux and Mac. No need for fancy bullet points.

The exciting Gumpo Deluxe release!
- Can collapse nested entries now
- Minor style changes and button added to the List Toolbar

END UP GUMPO DELUXE RELEASE UPDATE LIST OF FEATURES

Massive changes. Probably for the better. Should work seamlessly.
- Added manual sorting and nesting to all types
- Rewrote list load logic to be cleaner (will get to the others later)
- Moved jQuery declaration out to a separate file for loading dependent
  files
- Removed dropdown from Locations due to WORTHLESS NOW.
- Removed some console logging.
- Probably some other shit
- Caught a fixed a few bugs as well.
- Styles added for a few things, including proper cursors for add and
  remove item buttons.
- Moved search and add bar to the top of the list.

Whew. There's probably more. Really this time. I just forgot. Did a lot of legwork tonight.

Some fixes and file handling.
- Add single-instance mode [53ef22e4b4a79019b80700b3ad333f86b8e35e35]
- Handle files opened via double-click [53ef22e4b4a79019b80700b3ad333f86b8e35e35]

- Fixed bug with loading Place list [53ef22e4b4a79019b80700b3ad333f86b8e35e35]

HEY! Maybe this will be the end of it for now

Decided that this bad boy needed version checking... SO!
- Added version checking [631dc8bf22b9b649a11c606d0f3eb4722ec7e283]
- Immediately fixed an error in the version checking [790279cd0289f4b684ca3503f084862b0efa1543]

Talk about service.

Don't think I even made it an hour. Found some bugs. Fixed 'em. Added some stuff.
- Auto select newly added item [7efe291c181a544f91326cfd62df5e54cc291e16]
- Auto scroll-to newly added item [7efe291c181a544f91326cfd62df5e54cc291e16]
- Fixed logic behind selection after removal [7efe291c181a544f91326cfd62df5e54cc291e16]
- Auto scroll to selected-after-removal item... that's a good sentence. [7efe291c181a544f91326cfd62df5e54cc291e16]

That's probably it. Just cleaning shit up now that I'm actually testing the application properly.

Not convinced I've ever kept a promise.
- Changed sorting to Alphabetical [5afb618173ceb12809847204e7ba38963099a2b4]

Maybe the real last one this time.

Okay last one for the day. Promise.

And that's it.

Actually working release. All others deleted. Because I'm stupid.

WORKED ON DEV. HURRR HURRR. That's me. That's what I did.

Not massive changes, but they do some things.
- Nesting fix
- Save beforeunload
- Some styling junk as well.

releases.name: Initial Release
releases.body:
Hopefully fairly bug free. I will be adding features as I think of them.

Please feel free to request new features or report bugs by adding an Issue.

For those wondering, the file format is nothing special. A JSON file in a zip. Change the name to .zip and you can pull it out and edit it as you like.
